[thinking] **Clarifying AutoValue requirements**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about the requirements of AutoValue, which needs to avoid private or nested static classes. If I place it inside a public test class, I should declare the abstract static class Person with package-private access. If it’s nested in public, it can have default access, and AutoValue will still handle it. The generated class will likely be package-private, and my test can access it. So, needing Person.create to be package-private sounds fine!
